      • obtainConfidence

        protected double[] obtainConfidence(int x,
                                    int y,
                                    double[] example)
        Computes and returns the confidence vector for a given example for the classification class x vs class y. The vector is two-dimensional. The first position is the confidence for the class x and the second for the class y.
        Parameters:
        x - first class in the classification.
        y - second class in the classification.
        example - example given to compute the matrix.
        Returns:
        OVA vector for the given example.

      • ovo_table

        protected double[][] ovo_table(double[] example)
        Computes and returns the one-vs-one matrix for a given example. In this matrix, the value table[x][y] represents the confidence of the fact that the example given belong to the class x in the classification x vs y.
        Parameters:
        example - example given to compute the matrix.
        Returns:
        OVO matrix for the given example.

      • ova_table

        protected double[] ova_table(double[] example)
        Computes and returns the one-vs-all vector for a given example. In this vector, the value table[x] represents the confidence of the fact that the example given belong to the class x in the classification x vs the rest.
        Parameters:
        example - example given to compute the matrix.
        Returns:
        OVA vector for the given example.
